          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-dda248eba17c43f7971771c10c4960ef",
            "component": {
              "name": "Text",
              "options": {
                "text": "<p>Chi Tran joined smart furniture business Autonomous to build out its ecommerce operations as CMO almost seven years ago, soon after it was founded. Autonomous’ sleek work pods and standing desks – which have been sold directly to more than 600,000 customers in more than 100 countries via&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.autonomous.ai/?ref=solana.ghost.io\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Autonomous.ai</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;– are in high demand right now, but Tran knows that she needs to always be planning for the future.</p><p>She’s long viewed crypto as the future foundation for payments in commerce. In fact, in 2017, Autonomous designed and built the first version of a “crypto payment stack”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/ninjadotorg/handshake-protocol?ref=solana.ghost.io\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">with a set of open Ethereum smart contracts</a>. They got zero orders. She knew if she did it again, she’d need a blockchain that prioritized low-latency, high-throughput, and low-fees.</p><p>When the Autonomous team saw Solana, they knew they had the ideal candidate.</p><p>“As much as we were excited about deploying the 2017 crypto payment stack on Autonomous, it was a different world,” Tran said. “Fast forward to 2022 and it’s so different. More people have crypto, wallets are more popular, USDC is growing exponentially, a lot of composable smart contracts can supercharge the user experience, and there’s Solana.”</p><p>Tran put a team to work on redesigning their payment stack with Solana and Solana Pay, a new decentralized permissionless payments rail, making it easy for merchants to transact digital dollars like USDC for a fraction of a penny and without intermediaries at the point of sale (<a href=\"https://solana.com/news/solana-pay-update-march-2022?ref=solana.ghost.io\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">read more here about the latest with Solana Pay</a>).</p>"
              }
            },
